                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-34-victim336 t18120916-34-viclabel189"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-34-victim337 t18120916-34-viclabel189"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-34-victim338 t18120916-34-viclabel189"></join>. My partners are Spark Moline and John Gester. The prisoner has been occasionally employed by us a year and a half; he was in out employ at the time he was detected. On the 7th of July, about a quarter before six in the evening, from suspicion, I directed the officer to search the prisoner. He found a pound of wool concealed in his trowsers. The prisoner pleaded guilty.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you say it would be better for him if he confessed or worse if he did not - A. No.</p>
               <p>Q. Was it your wool - A. It was in my charge, and the same sort we had remaining. I never found any thing against him until that moment.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I beg for mercy.</p>
